CONTEXT NavMenuGrouping IN ENGLISH

PURPOSE CONTEXT NavMenuGrouping
{+Regression vehicle for issue #406 (navigation menu grouping by interface expression type).
This model mixes the two kinds of SESSION interfaces:
- task screens (expression subset of I[SESSION]): SearchRequirements, UpcomingRequirements
- lists (expression subset of V[SESSION*Concept]): Countries, Organisms, ProductForms,
  Requirements, Suppliers
With setting frontend.menuGrouping=byType the five lists must group under one "Lists"
menu item; the two task screens must stay top-level. With frontend.menuGrouping=none
(default) the menu must stay a flat list. See test/regression/issue-406/test.mjs.+}

REPRESENT Name TYPE ALPHANUMERIC

RELATION countryName[Country*Name] [UNI]
RELATION organismName[Organism*Name] [UNI]
RELATION productName[Product*Name] [UNI]
RELATION requirementName[Requirement*Name] [UNI]
RELATION supplierName[Supplier*Name] [UNI]
RELATION sessionQuery[SESSION*Name] [UNI]

-- A role, so that sessions have an active role and menu items are visible
-- (mirrors the hello-world test project)
ROLE User MAINTAINS AlwaysSatisfied
RULE AlwaysSatisfied : I[Country] |- I[Country]

--[Task screens: SESSION as target concept -> stay top-level]--
INTERFACE SearchRequirements LABEL "Search requirements" : "_SESSION"[SESSION] cRud BOX<FORM>
    [ "Search" : sessionQuery cRUd
    ]

INTERFACE UpcomingRequirements LABEL "Upcoming requirements" : "_SESSION"[SESSION] cRud BOX<FORM>
    [ "Query" : sessionQuery cRud
    ]

--[Lists: domain concept as target -> grouped with menuGrouping=byType]--
INTERFACE Countries : V[SESSION*Country] cRud BOX<TABLE>
    [ "Name" : countryName cRUd
    ]

INTERFACE Organisms : V[SESSION*Organism] cRud BOX<TABLE>
    [ "Name" : organismName cRUd
    ]

INTERFACE ProductForms LABEL "Product forms" : V[SESSION*Product] cRud BOX<TABLE>
    [ "Name" : productName cRUd
    ]

INTERFACE Requirements : V[SESSION*Requirement] cRud BOX<TABLE>
    [ "Name" : requirementName cRUd
    ]

INTERFACE Suppliers : V[SESSION*Supplier] cRud BOX<TABLE>
    [ "Name" : supplierName cRUd
    ]

POPULATION countryName CONTAINS
    [ ("nl", "Netherlands")
    , ("be", "Belgium")
    ]

ENDCONTEXT
